net.casper.io.file.in

Class CBuildFromFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.casper.io.file.in.CBuildFromFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.casper.data.model.CBuilder

    public class CBuildFromFile
extends Object
implements net.casper.data.model.CBuilder
    Loads a casper dataset from a file based on the file type. The type of the file is determined by its extension, and the appropriate file builder is used. Currently supported file types are XLS, XLSX, CSV. Types of columns in files may be specified or unspecified (in which case the widest possible type is used for loading values, eg: Object or String). Column names may be specified (allowing reading of only certain columns from a file) or unspecified (in which case all columns names do not need to be known in advance and all columns are loaded). Missing values are supporting in files via the use of optional cell readers.
    Version:
    $Revision: 147 $
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

      • CBuildFromFile

        public CBuildFromFile(File file)
               throws IOException
        Create file builder. Container name is the file name and will read column header from the file and load all columns. Columns will be of whatever type is provided by the underlying file reader. No primary key column.
        Parameters:
        file - file
        Throws:
        IOException - if IO problem reading file header.

      • CBuildFromFile

        public CBuildFromFile(File file,
              String primaryKeys)
               throws IOException
        Create file builder. Container name is the file name and will read column header from the file and load all columns. Columns will be of whatever type is provided by the underlying file reader.
        Parameters:
        file - file
        primaryKeys - null if no primary key otherwise the column names of primary keys, separated by comma, eg: "firstname,lastname" NB: do not include a space after the comma.
        Throws:
        IOException - if IO problem reading file header.

      • CBuildFromFile

        public CBuildFromFile(File file,
              String containerName,
              String[] columnNames,
              org.omancode.rmt.cellreader.CellReader<?>[] cellReaders,
              String[] primaryKeys)
               throws IOException
        Construct a casper file builder.
        Parameters:
        file - file
        containerName - if null will use default (the file name)
        columnNames - the name of the columns in the file. If null, column names will be loaded from the file header. If specified then the file must have a header with the same columns names (case and order insensitive).
        cellReaders - cell readers for each column. If null, the default cell readers for the file type will be used (ie: type returned is determined by the underlying file reader).
        primaryKeys - null if no primary key otherwise an array of primary key names
        Throws:
        IOException - if IO problem reading file header.
